The accident took place after the Buccleuch Interchange in Midrand.&nbsp;&quot;It's believed that one of the taxi's back tyres burst and the driver lost control, causing the taxi to roll multiple times before a truck collided with it,&quot; said EMER-G-MED. Shortly before 1pm EMER-G-MED&nbsp;dispatched a response vehicle as well as multiple ambulances to the scene.&nbsp;&quot;On assessment paramedics found that the seventeen patients, including a one-month-old child, had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate and they were treated at the scene before being transported to various nearby hospitals for further care,&quot; said EMER-G-MED.&nbsp;Johannesburg Metro Police Ddepartment were at the scene to investigate further.African News Agency